So, after getting the processed string, we can read it as n.

Once n is obtained, compute the sum as per the second Java program. The second Java program's code is:

for (int i = 1; i < n + 1; i++) {
    ans += (long) i * ((long) n / (long) i) * (((long) n / (long) i) + 1) / 2;
} Wait, the loop is from 1 to n inclusive.
